All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
AcademicInfo
The AcademicInfo class is used to define various academic information associated with the lecture.
App
The App class launches the stage, sets the main menu scene and manages the GUI components and events in the scene.
ControllerConvertFile
The ControllerConvertFile class manages the GUI components and events in the ConvertFile scene.
ControllerCreateSchedule
ControllerCreateSchedule is a controller class for the Create Schedule page.
ControllerImportSchedule
The ControllerUploadSchedule class manages the GUI components and events in the UploadSchedule scene.
ControllerLoadFileBeforeCreateSchedule
The ControllerLoadFileBeforeCreateSchedule class manages the GUI components and events in the loadFileBeforeCreateSchedule scene.
ControllerOverlayed
The Overlayed class is a JavaFX controller that manages the GUI components and events in a scene that displays information about overlapping and overcrowded lectures in a schedule.
ControllerViewSchedule
The ViewSchedule class is the controller for the ViewSchedule.fxml file.
ControllerWebCall
The ControllerWebCall class manages the GUI components and events in the WebCall scene.
Lecture
The Lecture class is used to manage all the information regarding a lecture.
Room
The Room class is used to define the name and capacity of the room where the lecture is scheduled to be.
Schedule
The Schedule class is used to represent a schedule of lectures for a student.
TimeSlot
The TimeSlot class is used to define the beginning and ending time of a lecture.
